B = data('sc4snmp.IP-MIB.ipInDiscards', rollup='latest').delta().sum(by=['host.name']).publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = data('sc4snmp.IP-MIB.ipOutRequests', rollup='latest').delta().sum(by=['host.name']).publish(label='C', enable=False)
D = data('sc4snmp.IP-MIB.ipOutNoRoutes', rollup='latest').delta().sum(by=['host.name']).publish(label='D', enable=False)
E = data('sc4snmp.IP-MIB.ipOutDiscards', rollup='latest').delta().sum(by=['host.name']).publish(label='E', enable=False)
F = (C-(D+E)).publish(label='F', enable=False)
H = (B/A*100).publish(label='H')
I = (E/C*100).publish(label='I')

ICMP (internet control message protocol)


These charts focus on the inbound traffic metrics. This information is collected by Splunk Connect for SNMP

chart.description: Packets/second count per interface (mulitcast / broadcast)
chart.name: Outbound Non-Unicast Packet Rate
chart.programText:
A = data('sc4snmp.IF-MIB.ifOutNUcastPkts').delta().sum(by=['host.name', 'ifIndex']).publish(label='A', enable=False)
B = (A).count(by=['host.name', 'ifIndex']).integrate().publish(label='B', enable=False)
C = (A/B).publish(label='C')
